               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Dǝrsāna Mikāʾel, Homiliary for the feasts of St Michael (fols.
                     1ra-108rb)
 I-1) Introduction and ʾarke-hymn (fols. 1ra-4vb)
 I-2)
                     Homily by Timothy (Damātewos), [Patriarch] of Alexandria [for Ḫǝdār] and
                     ʾarke-hymn (fols. 6ra-13vb); miracle (fol. 15ra-vb); commemorative notice (fol.
                     16ra-va); ʾarke-hymn (fol. 16va-vb)
 I-3) Homily by Metropolitan Yoḥannǝs
                     the Orthodox for the 12th of Tāḫśāś [Miyāzyā] and ʾarke-hymn (fols. 17ra-21vb);
                     miracle (fols. 22va-23b); commemorative notice (fols. 23va-24rb); ʾarke-hymn
                     (fol. 24rb)
 I-4) Homily by an anonymous author for the 12th of Ṭǝrr
                     [Tāḫśāś] and ʾarke-hymn (fols. 25ra-30rb); miracle (fol. 31ra-rb);
                     commemorative notice (fol. 32ra-rb); ʾarke-hymn (fol. 32rb)
 I-5) Homily by
                     an anonymous author for the 12th of Yakkātit and ʾarke-hymn (fols. 33ra-36ra);
                     miracle (fols. 36va-37rb); commemorative notice (fol. 38ra-rb); ʾarke-hymn
                     (fol. 38rb)
 I-6) Homily by Yoḥannǝs [Severus], Metropolitan [Patriarch] of
                     Antiochia for the 12th of Maggābit and ʾarke-hymn (fols. 39ra-51vb); miracle
                     (fols. 52va-53rb); commemorative notice (fol. 54ra); ʾarke-hymn (fol.
                     54ra-rb)
 I-7) Homily [by Epiphanius, Metropolitan of Cyprus] for the 12th
                     of Miyāzyā [Ṭǝrr] and ʾarke-hymn (fols. 55ra-57vb, 59ra-61rb); miracle (fols.
                     58ra-rb, 62ra-vb); commemorative notice (fol. 63ra-rb); ʾarke-hymn (fol.
                     63rb)
 I-8) Homily by Yoḥannǝs, Metropolitan of Ethiopia for Gǝnbot and
                     ʾarke-hymn (fols. 64ra-65rb); miracle (fols. 66ra-67rb); commemorative notice
                     (fol. 68ra-rb); ʾarke-hymn (fol. 68rb)
 I-9) Homily by Yoḥannǝs,
                     Metropolitan of Aksum (ʾAkʷǝsǝm) [for Sane] and ʾarke-hymn (fols. 69ra-74rb);
                     miracle (fol. 75ra-vb); commemorative notice (fols. 76va-77rb); ʾarke-hymn
                     (fol. 77rb)
 I-10) Homily by Metropolitan Yoḥannǝs for Ḥamle and ʾarke-hymn
                     (fols. 78ra-82rb); miracle (fol. 83ra-vb); commemorative notice (fol. 84va-vb);
                     ʾarke-hymn (fols. 84vb-85ra)
 I-11) Homily by an anonymous author for
                     Naḥāse and ʾarke-hymn (fols. 86ra-89rb); miracle (fol. 90ra-vb); commemorative
                     notice (fol. 92ra-rb); ʾarke-hymn (fol. 92rb)
 I-12) Homily by an anonymous
                     author for Maskaram and ʾarke-hymn (fols. 93ra-95vb); miracle (fols.
                     96vb-97rb); commemorative notice (fol. 97va); ʾarke-hymn (fol. 97va-vb)
                     I-13) Homily by an anonymous author for Ṭǝqǝmt and ʾarke-hymn (fols.
                     98va-101vb, 105ra-106rb); miracle (fol. 106va-vb); commemorative notice (fols.
                     107va-108rb); ʾarke-hymn (fol. 108rb)
 
 Additiones 1-3.</summary>
