                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#109va">f. 109va</locus>
                           <desc>: Protective prayer against "anxiety" (Ḥǝmamä dǝngaḍe).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#109va">109va</locus>: ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ድንጋጼ፡ ባርከኒ፡
                              ክርስቶስ፡ ርድአኒ፡ ወአድኅነኒ፡ እማእምቀ፡ ምድር፡ ወተነቀፍ፡ ወውግረተ፡ እብን፡...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is written in the same hand as Additiones 2 and 3. The
                              names of Walda Māryām and Kidāna Māryām are written over erasure.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#109vb">f. 109vb</locus>
                           <desc>: Protective prayer against eye disease (Ḥǝmamä ʿayn).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#109vb">109vb</locus>: ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ዐይን፡ የአሐጂም፡
                              ያቀሐጂም፡ ኮክሞስ፡ እልንዱስ፡ እልቅንቶስ፡ ራአት፡ ዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ፡ አደኅኖ[sic]፡ ለገብርከ፡ ወልደ፡
                              ማርያም፡ ...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is written in the same hand as Additiones 1 and 3. The
                              name of Walda Māryām is written over erasure. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#110ra">f. 110ra</locus>
                           <desc>: Protective prayer against the evil eye (Ḥǝmamä ʿaynät).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#110ra">110ra</locus>: በስመ፡”… አልካሸዕታ፡ ወካሸዕታ፡ የአቲጂ፡
                              አድኅነኒ፡ እምቦለድ፡ ለገብርከ፡ ወልደ፡ ማርያም፡ በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ዓይነት፡ ...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is written in Gǝʿǝz and Amharic, in the same hand as
                              Additiones 2 and 3. The names of Walda Māryām and Gabra ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer
                              are written over erasure. </note>
                        </item>
